properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 4 at 1:00PM PST until January 7 at 12:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...East winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts to 60 mph. Isolated
gusts to 70 mph at the most wind prone locations.

* WHERE...San Diego County Mountains and Foothills.

* WHEN...From midnight Sunday night to noon PST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Difficult driving conditions for high profile vehicles
on I-8 through the mountains, on Highway 78 from Ramona to
Julian, and on Highway 94 from Jamul to Campo.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The Santa Ana winds will be strongest at
the usual wind prone mountain sites like Sill Hill, Palomar
Mountain and Big Black Mountain. Gusts to 70 mph are possible at
these locations.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT SUNDAY NIGHT TO NOON PST TUESDAY
